[src:atlantic-ocean/atlantic-ocean-p02] In the southwest Atlantic, a peak was reached in the mid-1980s and catches now fluctuate between 1.7 and 2.6 million tons.
[src:atlantic-ocean/atlantic-ocean-p02] , which reached half a million tons in 2013 or half the peak value, is considered fully fished to overfished.
